Resolv, Morpho vaults, and many carry products have a clean underlying mechanism but messy wrapper-level fragility. Keep those as separate rows or separate tables.

A sharper schema would be:

`leg = type | immediate payer -> ultimate source | mechanism | primary short-risk | secondary risks | gross source | main drags | break condition`

`edge = from_leg -> to_leg | edge_type`

`wrapper = concentration | correlation | redemption priority | governance control | opacity`

